docs.text: " rebel without a cause " is such an important film in american history because it is a true analysis of youth in america that everyone of all ages can relate to .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: everyone feels that they are different in some way , that they don't belong in some places and " rebel without a cause " successfully shows on screen these universal emotions .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: no matter what generation you belong to , these feelings are present .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this is why james dean is admired by america , because in this film he represents us all and his actions are actions that we would also execute .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in our minds , we just try to do the right thing just like dean's jim stark does .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: not only does " rebel without a cause " display these universal emotions for all to relate to but it also shows that america has suffered a uniqe pattern in its social structure .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: each generation looks at its past generation without a strong connection .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this is because times change and in response people change .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: no matter how popular you were once , as your generation grows older , newer breeds look at you in a different light .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this is why stark and his friends never could form a strong relationship with their parents .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even if their parents insisted that they were also rebellious and troublesome in the past , the teens could not believe this .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in one humorous scene , stark , his girlfriend judy ( natalie wood ) , and his pal plato ( sal mineo ) pretend they are adults .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they use upper class british accents and in their conversations they make it out to appear that kids are no good and should be ignored .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this scene shows that what was once cool in a past generation is the complete opposite in another .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: speaking on behalf of my generation , i feel that dean has lost a lot of his coolness from our perspective as the years have grown by .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the only ones who seem to still lionize him are those members of his generation . same
docs.label: positive

docs.text: goes for brando , redford , even deniro .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i can only imagine how vaguely matt damon , ben affleck , and brad pitt will be viewed at the mid point of the twenty first century .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: will dean even be remembered when these newcomers are forgotten ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: any film that sparks this kind of thought is certainly a milestone in american film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even if " rebel without a cause " has some ridiculous scenes ( the game of chicken - did people really act this way ? ) , an unbelievable conclusion ( how did everyone end up at the abandoned mansion at the end ? ) , and a silly romance ( wood declares her love for dean after talking to him for a couple hours ) it still is a fabulous film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the acting is so believable that it is no wonder that dean was considered the epitome of cool .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: now , however , the coolness is fading . . .
docs.label: positive
